<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10145k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10145k">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10145k"> 145(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sweet by &amp; by</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;I know two good men who had a rare royal time together for years, yet Brother A.&apos;s favourite tune was, &ldquo;In the <mark>sweet by and by</mark>,&rdquo; and Brother B.&apos;s, &ldquo;In the sweet Now and Now.&rdquo; When Brother A. saw the rain, he would unerringly surmise, &ldquo;This will make mud,&rdquo; then Brother B. would chime in, &ldquo;This will lay the dust.&rdquo; <small> Daniel Crawford, <a name="DCTB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DCTB"><cite title="source">Thinking Black</cite></a> (1912) 212</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
